WEBVTT

00:04.098 --> 00:05.180
Well, good morning, Rich Woods.

00:05.220 --> 00:12.551
This is one thing that I am for certain.

00:13.753 --> 00:16.878
Almost every single one of us would agree.

00:18.640 --> 00:25.991
Our lives are loud, and we are weary.

00:27.153 --> 00:28.095
Anybody else feel that?

00:29.657 --> 00:32.882
Our lives are loud, and we

00:33.186 --> 00:36.132
Our weary, my good friend Ali says the word tender.

00:36.192 --> 00:38.437
We're just a tender people.

00:38.497 --> 00:46.093
And as people, we live in constant information, right?

00:46.133 --> 00:54.610
Some we go out and get, some is just constantly given to us, but we are constantly surrounded by noise.

00:54.914 --> 00:57.177
And that noise takes on at different things.

00:57.258 --> 01:02.766
But one of the things that I know is that we have so much information coming at us all the time.

01:03.126 --> 01:06.191
And what we sometimes want is quiet.

01:07.673 --> 01:10.858
And what that looks like sometimes is compassion.

01:11.779 --> 01:14.504
And as Darren said, that's what we are going to be talking about today.

01:14.564 --> 01:21.394
Because as people, we're surrounded by things like opinions and outrage and advice

01:21.570 --> 01:25.335
and content and thoughts and voices and phones.

01:25.675 --> 01:27.758
And I could go on and on and on.

01:27.818 --> 01:31.303
And this leads itself to our selfish nature.

01:32.684 --> 01:35.428
Which, if anybody is in the room and was like, what?

01:35.488 --> 01:36.429
We're selfish.

01:36.830 --> 01:37.270
Sorry.

01:37.310 --> 01:39.193
We're selfish.

01:40.595 --> 01:40.815
Right?

01:40.855 --> 01:41.776
It's how we're created.

01:43.478 --> 01:49.426
But that selfishness sometimes pushes us to walk by things like this.

01:53.346 --> 01:59.255
We can feel completely alone in a crowd like we're in today or somewhere like this.

02:01.898 --> 02:06.004
And because of the constant stimulation, we just settle in.

02:06.044 --> 02:11.532
We say, okay, we give up and we become numb.

02:11.592 --> 02:21.106
And the noise that makes us feel so safe that we just continue on with that exchange and we just stay

02:21.282 --> 02:24.027
completely plugged in to this.

02:27.372 --> 02:30.357
Now none of us in this room are surprised.

02:32.240 --> 02:39.372
Yet more people than ever are anxious and unseen and directionless and exhausted and alone.

02:39.412 --> 02:44.440
And the saddest part about that is this isn't adults, friends.

02:45.061 --> 02:45.983
This isn't just our adults.

02:46.804 --> 02:47.826
We see kids

02:48.226 --> 02:52.513
eight years old, 10 years old, nine years old, taking their own lives, and why?

02:52.573 --> 02:53.614
Because they feel alone.

02:54.696 --> 02:56.980
Because no one really saw them.

02:57.701 --> 03:04.251
Well, today in our host passage, we're gonna see and Matthew this idea of Jesus looking at a crowd.

03:05.673 --> 03:13.185
And weirdly enough, the crowd that he saw all those thousands of years ago looks very similar to the crowd we see today.

03:13.245 --> 03:16.370
Because they were people, just like us.

03:16.930 --> 03:24.498
And they did things just like we do, but how Jesus reacts to them and sees them is a little bit different than what we do today.

03:25.299 --> 03:27.661
See, he doesn't look at the crowd when he comes on them.

03:27.701 --> 03:33.467
He's going to the Sermon on the Mount and he goes up there and there's all these people following him, which they have been for days.

03:33.847 --> 03:36.891
And he says, what is wrong with you people?

03:37.091 --> 03:38.753
Why are you following me?

03:38.773 --> 03:38.953
No.

03:41.656 --> 03:44.018
He doesn't look at the crowd and roll his eyes.

03:44.162 --> 03:45.664
Any other eye rollers out here?

03:45.824 --> 03:48.207
I'm one of them, so I feel very convicted right now.

03:49.929 --> 03:51.170
He doesn't call them lazy.

03:51.210 --> 03:56.256
He doesn't just announce for them to suck it up or try harder.

03:58.038 --> 04:04.606
This shows compassion in everything that he does because this is our Jesus.

04:07.670 --> 04:11.154
So Matthew 9, 36, it says, when he saw the crowds,

04:11.298 --> 04:17.664
He had compassion on them because they were harassed and helpless, like sheep without a shepherd.

04:17.965 --> 04:25.932
Now harassed and helpless maybe aren't used necessarily so frequent in our language, but we say things that mean the same thing.

04:27.554 --> 04:34.201
And actually the longer that the world is in the state that it's in, these actually do become more said.

04:35.182 --> 04:39.666
Now if we go at the very beginning, when he saw the crowds, this phrase really matters.

04:40.066 --> 04:43.411
Because it tells us how Jesus saw people.

04:44.372 --> 04:46.515
He saw them with compassion.

04:47.376 --> 04:52.784
So before we go any further, I want to kind of define what this idea of compassion means.

04:53.465 --> 04:58.972
Because we have a lot of things that we use the word compassion for that actually might be empathy.

04:58.992 --> 04:59.914
It might be gentleness.

04:59.974 --> 05:00.895
It might be something else.

05:01.135 --> 05:03.298
And what we want to talk about today is compassion.

05:03.859 --> 05:05.842
So I'm going to put this

05:05.922 --> 05:09.207
Greek word for compassion that we see all over the gospels.

05:09.227 --> 05:10.248
And we're going to talk about that.

05:10.489 --> 05:13.814
But I'm going to put it on the screen because I'm not going to say it out loud because it really is funny.

05:14.174 --> 05:14.635
Here we go.

05:15.256 --> 05:17.980
Splagno, am I, right?

05:18.040 --> 05:19.402
That's how you say it.

05:19.903 --> 05:23.428
We're just going to leave it there because actually I don't speak Greek, so we're just going to leave it there.

05:24.530 --> 05:25.752
But here's what this means.

05:26.353 --> 05:32.722
This word Matthew uses in the Scripture when he writes literally first to a gut reaction.

05:33.026 --> 05:37.992
the inner most part of his body, a deep seated emotion.

05:39.214 --> 05:44.540
So what we see when Jesus saw the crowd is he says he saw the crowd and he had compassion on them.

05:44.861 --> 05:48.305
What it doesn't say is he was mildly concerned about them.

05:50.027 --> 05:55.414
What it doesn't say is he kind of thought about what he might do for them.

05:57.417 --> 05:58.578
He moves.

05:58.978 --> 06:03.142
He moves in this gut deep physical, eternal reaction.

06:03.202 --> 06:07.066
And that is the same word that we see multiple times in the gospels.

06:08.127 --> 06:13.312
In Matthew 141, we see the leperate says, moved with compassion, this same word.

06:13.713 --> 06:15.374
Jesus reached out and touched him.

06:15.715 --> 06:17.056
Jesus sees the man.

06:17.076 --> 06:19.258
He moves towards the man.

06:19.298 --> 06:21.921
And then his compassion heals him.

06:21.961 --> 06:27.346
He touches and he heals what was considered untouchable and unredeemable.

06:28.002 --> 06:30.324
Do we do that in our lives?

06:31.605 --> 06:37.071
Do we actually make emotion and a movement towards people that we feel don't deserve it?

06:38.372 --> 06:39.553
And the answer is we don't.

06:40.574 --> 06:44.398
In Matthew 14, 14, we see him feeding the crowd and he has compassion.

06:44.758 --> 06:47.761
Same word on them and healed their sick.

06:48.081 --> 06:50.223
You know what was happening when Jesus was on the mountain?

06:50.323 --> 06:51.545
He was tired.

06:51.605 --> 06:57.170
Just like us, he had a human body just like us.

06:57.730 --> 06:59.112
And he was tired.

06:59.152 --> 07:01.256
He wanted rest.

07:02.237 --> 07:03.940
But you know what we know about compassion?

07:04.361 --> 07:07.105
Sometimes compassion interrupts our plans.

07:08.087 --> 07:12.795
Sometimes, and we see this in Scripture, compassion interrupts Jesus' plans.

07:13.917 --> 07:17.002
Because the truth of the matter is compassion can be inconvenient.

07:18.504 --> 07:19.446
And it's costly.

07:21.209 --> 07:24.434
But compassion is what we want to move.

07:25.346 --> 07:35.761
This is a motion that demands a response because the truth is compassion is love that moves towards suffering.

07:37.644 --> 07:42.471
And that is what we're going to capture all of our message about today.

07:42.531 --> 07:48.200
It's this idea that we can't have compassion and not move towards suffering.

07:48.720 --> 07:51.825
It is seeing pain and refusing to stay unchanged.

07:52.165 --> 07:52.846
It's action.

07:53.267 --> 07:55.250
It's intentional and it's on purpose.

07:56.674 --> 08:03.442
So I thought of a couple real life ways that we might see something like this.

08:04.783 --> 08:11.811
Imagine seeing a child, small child, standing alone in a busy parking lot by himself crying.

08:15.756 --> 08:19.940
You don't just stop and analyze and wait for a minute.

08:20.521 --> 08:24.946
Maybe a split second to see if mom is like around, or dad is like around the car.

08:25.666 --> 08:27.609
But for the most part, what would most of us do?

08:28.290 --> 08:29.752
Go see what's going on, right?

08:29.772 --> 08:33.256
I would be the one to say, are you kidnapping that child?

08:33.276 --> 08:36.300
Because I probably would just grab it and be like, I don't know, we'll figure it out later.

08:36.340 --> 08:39.124
You move towards it.

08:40.226 --> 08:41.387
What about that phone call?

08:43.811 --> 08:52.903
Whether you know it's bad news, whether you're expecting bad news, you see that one name, that one time a day, you just know.

08:52.923 --> 08:55.186
It's a gut reaction.

08:55.394 --> 08:55.634
Right?

08:56.175 --> 08:59.239
You know that there's bad news on the other line.

09:01.162 --> 09:01.963
It moves you.

09:02.003 --> 09:05.487
It makes you physically feel sick.

09:06.649 --> 09:10.434
And this is the idea of compassion that we see in the scripture.

09:10.494 --> 09:12.677
That's stirring that gut-level pull.

09:12.697 --> 09:14.019
It's compassion.

09:14.039 --> 09:17.003
It actually won't let you walk away.

09:18.104 --> 09:22.450
And this is what Matthew means when he says that Jesus has compassion.

09:22.786 --> 09:28.432
Through this entire series, we've talked about a few other things like empathy and gentleness and proximity.

09:28.673 --> 09:34.199
So I wanted to make sure that we all know the difference of how all of those play together, because the truth of the matter is they do.

09:34.239 --> 09:35.560
They all play together.

09:36.942 --> 09:47.433
Because if we're going to take on the matters of the mission, which we are as a church, if we are going to walk into this year of overflow, which we are as a church, we have to know how all of these work.

09:48.154 --> 09:51.698
See, empathy says, I feel with you, so tell me more.

09:53.410 --> 09:53.610
Right?

09:53.630 --> 09:54.311
We all feel that.

09:55.513 --> 09:57.175
The world says, I don't have time for that.

09:59.938 --> 10:02.622
Gentleness says, I will respond with care.

10:04.284 --> 10:06.507
But the world says, say whatever.

10:06.827 --> 10:07.649
Your feelings don't matter.

10:10.252 --> 10:13.837
Compassion says, I am going to step toward you.

10:13.957 --> 10:15.339
I'm going to sit in that with you.

10:15.399 --> 10:21.106
And the world says, no, no, I'm going to protect me and I'm going to keep my distance.

10:23.010 --> 10:32.379
See, empathy feels, gentleness walks gently and tenderly and carefully and compassion moves.

10:34.381 --> 10:39.085
The problem is not the sheep that we see in our passage in Matthew.

10:40.707 --> 10:47.193
What Jesus sees and in his compassion that he's moved to recognize is that these are sheep without a shepherd.

10:47.993 --> 10:48.894
Is that the sheep's fault?

10:49.855 --> 10:50.035
No.

10:51.877 --> 10:52.818
It's the shepherd's fault.

10:54.082 --> 10:59.447
And so what he's saying wasn't actually an insult to the people.

11:00.488 --> 11:01.329
It was a fact.

11:02.230 --> 11:03.331
It was a diagnosis.

11:04.172 --> 11:11.519
What he says is they were helpless and harassed like a sheep without a shepherd.

11:11.879 --> 11:18.846
We see way back in Numbers 27, 16 and 17 in the Old Testament, it says, may the Lord appoint someone over this community.

11:18.886 --> 11:23.570
So the Lord's people will not be like sheep without a shepherd.

11:23.970 --> 11:27.135
See, this shows that wandering doesn't always mean rebellion.

11:27.195 --> 11:29.378
That's what we take, right?

11:29.398 --> 11:33.163
Now, did the people rebel in the Old Testament?

11:33.364 --> 11:33.925
They did.

11:33.965 --> 11:39.693
They wandered for 40 days and 40 nights because they wanted to not obey.

11:39.733 --> 11:44.981
And Jesus, God in His goodness, gave them all of the things that they needed.

11:45.081 --> 11:51.250
He said, I'll give you fire, I'll give you a cloud, I'll give you whatever, and they were still like selfish.

11:54.498 --> 11:57.542
But then in God's goodness, again, he sends Jesus.

11:57.602 --> 12:01.667
And so there's the distinction between what was happening here in Numbers.

12:02.007 --> 12:05.371
What the people in the Old Testament knew is there is a Messiah coming.

12:07.253 --> 12:08.455
And we know it.

12:09.196 --> 12:10.297
And we believe it.

12:11.078 --> 12:17.566
And so in this scripture, it's saying that they know that the Lord's people will not be like sheep without a shepherd anymore.

12:20.189 --> 12:24.434
Because sometimes that means rebellion, but sometimes it just means that no one's guiding.

12:25.186 --> 12:26.188
No one's protecting.

12:26.228 --> 12:28.311
No one's caring.

12:30.636 --> 12:36.125
In Ezekiel 34, 11, it says, I myself will search for my sheep and look after them.

12:37.087 --> 12:39.211
Again, we see that God does not blame the sheep.

12:39.271 --> 12:41.234
He confronts the shepherd who abandoned them.

12:42.210 --> 12:44.433
And this is sometimes is our humanness.

12:44.473 --> 12:53.787
We have to remember when we say like, we don't deserve God's love and well, you don't know what I've done and God doesn't see me the way that he sees everyone else because I don't deserve it.

12:54.087 --> 12:54.928
Here's the truth.

12:55.128 --> 12:59.274
God's frustration is never aimed at wounded sheep.

13:00.937 --> 13:02.940
It is aimed at absent shepherds.

13:03.781 --> 13:07.346
But here's the problem Christ followers that call ourselves Christians.

13:07.746 --> 13:10.290
We are sometimes the shepherds doing the wounding.

13:12.514 --> 13:16.378
And what we want to say is no compassion, gentleness.

13:16.899 --> 13:21.524
The matters of the mission is what moves me to do the things that I do.

13:21.604 --> 13:24.947
So let's look at the host passes one more time in Matthew 9, 36.

13:25.248 --> 13:31.574
When Jesus saw the crowds, he had compassion on them because they were harassed and helpless, like sheep without a shepherd.

13:31.995 --> 13:33.917
So in proximity, he sees them.

13:35.799 --> 13:38.442
In empathy, he feels their condition.

13:39.663 --> 13:42.386
In gentleness, he does not shame them.

13:43.394 --> 13:46.899
and showing compassion, he moves to act.

13:47.820 --> 13:52.788
See the love that Jesus had for them that he has for us refuses to stay distant.

13:54.490 --> 14:02.982
And I know that some of you that maybe are new to this Jesus thing, maybe some of you that have followed him a really long time, he's like, no, sometimes I feel him distant.

14:03.243 --> 14:03.984
You wanna know why?

14:04.024 --> 14:05.146
Because you're doing this.

14:06.968 --> 14:08.010
And God's doing this.

14:08.030 --> 14:10.994
And we're doing this.

14:12.290 --> 14:14.193
Why are you not close?

14:15.334 --> 14:17.177
Why are you not coming to my aid?

14:17.197 --> 14:18.999
Why are you not giving me the things that I want?

14:19.039 --> 14:20.541
Why are you not seeing me?

14:20.982 --> 14:22.564
And God's like, I went to the cross.

14:22.624 --> 14:23.786
I've seen you for a long time.

14:26.129 --> 14:30.996
But in our compassion, we stop because the truth is the matter.

14:31.096 --> 14:32.618
We're the ones pushing him away.

14:33.179 --> 14:34.260
Henry now says this.

14:36.203 --> 14:41.330
Compassion asks us to go where it hurts to enter places of pain.

14:43.234 --> 14:45.778
Y'all, we don't want to enter our own pain, right?

14:47.400 --> 14:48.061
It's hard.

14:48.922 --> 14:52.567
Let alone enter someone else's pain or go where it hurts.

14:53.889 --> 14:54.790
So what do we do?

14:54.810 --> 14:55.792
What do we do with this?

14:57.955 --> 14:58.676
We simply move.

15:00.318 --> 15:01.339
We move towards people.

15:03.182 --> 15:08.469
When your kids started to learn to walk, they did it one tiny step at a time.

15:09.130 --> 15:09.891
And guess what they did?

15:09.931 --> 15:11.794
They fell down, they got back up.

15:13.090 --> 15:13.811
They did it again.

15:13.831 --> 15:19.136
And that is what he's asking of us.

15:22.279 --> 15:25.202
If we slow down enough to see the need in the first place.

15:26.563 --> 15:31.148
And if we are brave enough to say, tell me more.

15:33.069 --> 15:37.934
We say that because that's one of the things that we say a lot around here.

15:37.974 --> 15:39.396
And we've told you that it's dangerous.

15:40.336 --> 15:41.938
We've told you that those words

15:42.114 --> 15:44.356
There's a good chance that people will tell you more.

15:45.858 --> 15:47.579
But where's your heart when you hear it?

15:49.701 --> 15:54.025
Because we can't just say it with the hope that they're not gonna actually respond.

15:55.086 --> 15:57.268
We have to say it with the hope that they do.

15:58.550 --> 16:07.278
So as Darren reminded us this morning, the actual definition of compassion is a deep, sympathetic awareness of another's suffering and misfortune.

16:07.979 --> 16:11.602
Combined with a strong desire and motivation to relieve that suffering,

16:12.514 --> 16:16.359
Moving on, just feeling bad to actively wanting to help.

16:16.379 --> 16:19.763
Compassion begins when we stop asking, what is wrong with all these people?

16:19.843 --> 16:20.824
Why is everyone an idiot?

16:23.968 --> 16:25.309
That was my dad's word if he's watching.

16:28.233 --> 16:32.278
And we start asking, what can I do to help?

16:33.539 --> 16:34.661
Now, hear me say this too.

16:34.721 --> 16:39.026
There are 400 people probably in this room.

16:41.922 --> 16:47.970
You are all created to do a thing in God's kingdom that only you can do.

16:48.090 --> 16:48.811
Did you know that?

16:49.792 --> 16:58.122
Not that other people don't have a same skillset, but there was something that you are put on this planet to do, and God wants you to do it, and this is it.

16:59.143 --> 17:01.206
What's something that I can do to help?

17:01.246 --> 17:03.969
Because your thing is not everybody else's thing.

17:04.810 --> 17:07.013
We all don't have the same financial background.

17:07.033 --> 17:10.898
We all don't have the same skillset, and that is what makes us beautiful.

17:11.874 --> 17:13.737
That is what makes this church beautiful.

17:14.017 --> 17:20.307
When we say we are for the city, we have to be for the city.

17:20.327 --> 17:22.811
This is not just words.

17:23.332 --> 17:31.665
If you've not been around Richwoods a long time, we are planting a church in the East Bluff because we are for the city.

17:31.685 --> 17:40.338
And we don't want to just be the church on North Knoxville or a church in Washington or a church on the other side of town that doesn't do what we say.

17:41.090 --> 17:43.694
And so we have to walk that road.

17:44.555 --> 17:46.638
We have to relieve that suffering.

17:47.039 --> 17:58.035
But when we live without the action of compassion, we can quickly and dangerously slip into something that even in the scripture Jesus warns us against.

17:59.197 --> 17:59.798
And what is that?

18:00.919 --> 18:03.403
Indifference or lukewarm.

18:04.204 --> 18:07.469
You know what Jesus says about being lukewarm about following him?

18:08.050 --> 18:08.451
No, thanks.

18:09.472 --> 18:10.834
I either want you in or I want you out.

18:12.130 --> 18:14.933
I want you in, all in or all out, I don't really care.

18:15.734 --> 18:17.636
But this whatever, no.

18:18.216 --> 18:19.738
This in between, no.

18:19.918 --> 18:26.204
This indifference, you're doing nothing for my kingdom when you just play whatever, right?

18:26.264 --> 18:34.793
Whatever is actually a really bad word in my house, I do not let people say it because usually it comes as a jab, right?

18:34.853 --> 18:36.815
What do you wanna do, whatever?

18:37.275 --> 18:38.637
Uh-uh, there's my eye roll, did you see it?

18:38.657 --> 18:40.018
You guys probably couldn't see it, but I did.

18:41.218 --> 18:51.409
Whatever is bad, because I think that you either just say what you mean, or you don't say anything at all, but this indifference is really hard.

18:52.170 --> 18:56.414
See, Ellie Weisel says the opposite of love is not hate, it's indifference.

18:59.558 --> 19:03.562
Indifferent sees pain and is unchanged.

19:04.483 --> 19:07.526
Compassion sees pain and is moved.

19:08.107 --> 19:10.930
What indifference does is make us think things like this.

19:11.682 --> 19:12.643
Well, someone else will handle it.

19:13.986 --> 19:15.207
That's not my responsibility.

19:16.189 --> 19:17.671
Well, I didn't cause that.

19:19.113 --> 19:20.415
I don't have the capacity.

19:20.435 --> 19:21.457
I don't have the time.

19:21.477 --> 19:22.979
I don't have the mental load.

19:22.999 --> 19:25.964
I, I, I, I, I.

19:29.069 --> 19:30.611
Do you know what Jesus is asking?

19:32.654 --> 19:34.076
Stop it with the eyes.

19:35.438 --> 19:38.763
The eyes is what makes us indifferent.

19:39.565 --> 19:40.466
Because it's all about us.

19:40.898 --> 19:55.475
So about what makes us, but what God is asking is, you let me pour into you as a Jesus follower, as the person, as a shepherd, and then you go do the things I'm asking you to do because then it's about the kingdom, it's not about you.

19:55.515 --> 20:01.361
It's about giving glory where glory is due and where is that to our Lord and Jesus Christ.

20:02.022 --> 20:03.043
That's where it's due.

20:03.984 --> 20:09.170
So when we take ourselves out, that is what we see.

20:10.114 --> 20:15.703
And as Darren said, there's no better story that really shows us that action than in Luke with the story of the Good Samaritan.

20:16.404 --> 20:18.026
So I wanted to read it together this morning.

20:18.547 --> 20:28.903
It says, Jesus replied, a man was going down from Jerusalem to Jericho, and he fell among robbers who stripped him and beat him and departed, leaving him half dead.

20:29.644 --> 20:32.969
Now, by chance, a priest was going down the road.

20:33.870 --> 20:36.274
And when he saw him, he passed by on the other side.

20:37.095 --> 20:38.898
So likewise, a Levite

20:39.010 --> 20:43.715
When he came to the place and saw him, passed by on the other side as well.

20:43.735 --> 20:49.061
But a Samaritan, as he journeyed, came to where he was and when he saw him, he had what?

20:49.662 --> 20:50.463
Compassion.

20:51.304 --> 20:59.993
He went to him and he bound up his wounds, pouring on oil and wine, then he sent him on his own animal and brought him to an inn and took care of him.

21:01.335 --> 21:05.880
Now the way that compassion works out in that is the whole arc.

21:06.721 --> 21:07.762
He saw him.

21:09.090 --> 21:10.391
He moved to action.

21:10.992 --> 21:13.495
He could have done one of those few things.

21:13.555 --> 21:20.542
He could have just done this or just done this or just done this, but he walked it all the way because that's where his compassion was.

21:21.203 --> 21:35.359
Now, you've probably heard, there's a good possibility you have heard the Good Samaritan preach multiple times, but this week, what I really was hit by is this idea that the Levite and the priests were actually maybe not cool.

21:37.601 --> 21:38.482
They were indifferent.

21:40.450 --> 21:47.241
Maybe they weren't just being violent or mean because it doesn't say that they were the ones that beat him.

21:47.601 --> 21:48.382
Those were the robbers.

21:49.504 --> 21:57.196
But when they walked by, they just were a little meh.

21:57.216 --> 21:58.859
They were simply unmoved.

21:59.961 --> 22:02.264
They saw and they passed by.

22:04.247 --> 22:08.434
See compassion moves towards pain and indifference walks around it.

22:12.226 --> 22:14.809
For a lot of us, the truth is we are guilty of it.

22:16.432 --> 22:17.493
We are guilty of it.

22:18.254 --> 22:22.499
It is hard to step into messy, but we are messy.

22:22.539 --> 22:39.762
And the hope that we have in Jesus and the idea that this world is not our home should lend itself to stop thinking someone else will do it and start thinking, but God has asked me to do it because that is the truth and he most certainly has.

22:40.322 --> 22:44.587
As a staff member, we say around here, we don't have to do this.

22:44.888 --> 22:47.251
We get to do this and we mean it.

22:48.092 --> 22:53.418
I get to stand up on this stage and share this message with you because that is how God gifted me.

22:55.020 --> 22:59.266
You get to do the things that you get to do because that is where you are.

22:59.306 --> 23:00.868
You get to go to work.

23:02.429 --> 23:04.492
Some of you are like, do I?

23:06.174 --> 23:06.575
You do.

23:08.377 --> 23:09.298
You get.

23:09.570 --> 23:17.758
To have meals with your family, you get to be in your family and on and on and on.

23:19.700 --> 23:24.424
But Jesus asks us a lot of things that we sometimes forget, so I'm just gonna give you a few.

23:24.744 --> 23:26.266
You know what Jesus asks us to do?

23:26.666 --> 23:28.028
Feed His sheep.

23:29.929 --> 23:31.271
You know what Jesus asks us to do?

23:31.311 --> 23:34.454
Do unto others is we would have done unto ourselves.

23:34.554 --> 23:35.635
We forget that one a lot.

23:37.456 --> 23:39.058
You know what Jesus asks us to do?

23:39.906 --> 23:40.867
Turn the other cheek.

23:41.688 --> 23:43.530
Oof.

23:43.550 --> 23:44.871
You want Jesus to ask us to do?

23:44.931 --> 23:49.015
To be shepherds and love his flock.

23:50.256 --> 23:54.721
Now please hear me say that moving towards compassion is hard, okay?

23:55.702 --> 24:00.847
This isn't like lovely, you know, skipping through the flowers kind of feel.

24:00.947 --> 24:01.728
It just isn't.

24:01.768 --> 24:03.289
It is hard.

24:04.030 --> 24:05.611
But it is what we are created to do.

24:05.651 --> 24:08.274
And when we live like Jesus and we apprentice under him,

24:08.930 --> 24:09.891
We can do it.

24:11.093 --> 24:12.055
You can do it.

24:12.555 --> 24:13.978
You can step into the Missy.

24:13.998 --> 24:15.520
You can step into the hard, why?

24:15.760 --> 24:18.605
Because God is asking you to, and He created you to.

24:20.267 --> 24:21.209
Those are two boxes.

24:21.789 --> 24:28.219
Pretty big ones, already checked.

24:28.239 --> 24:33.147
We can't do and take care of people in a space of indifference.

24:33.167 --> 24:35.871
Mother Teresa says, love cannot remain by itself.

24:36.992 --> 24:38.034
It has no meaning.

24:38.882 --> 24:41.066
Love has to be put into action.

24:42.428 --> 24:45.633
Now compassion and love, we kind of use these intermingled.

24:46.034 --> 24:47.776
We use the word love for different things.

24:47.837 --> 24:49.499
I love tacos and I love my husband.

24:49.539 --> 24:51.082
They mean different things.

24:52.684 --> 24:56.090
So please hear me say that love has to be put into action.

24:56.130 --> 25:05.025
In James 2 16, if one of you says to them, go in peace, keep warm and well fed, but does nothing about their physical need.

25:05.045 --> 25:05.906
What good is it?

25:06.338 --> 25:11.663
It's like someone coming to your door because their car broke down and they walked a mile to your door.

25:11.743 --> 25:16.488
You open it up and they're shivering and cold and you're like, I'll call AA, have a good day.

25:16.528 --> 25:17.969
Right?

25:17.989 --> 25:23.615
It's doing nothing to really see them in the moment.

25:24.656 --> 25:26.197
It's not bringing them a blanket.

25:26.257 --> 25:27.939
It's not saying come inside.

25:29.761 --> 25:31.122
It's saying that's not my problem.

25:31.743 --> 25:35.026
That's not my responsibility and someone else will probably do it.

25:38.050 --> 25:41.054
This is something that was so convicting to me this week.

25:43.217 --> 25:48.043
What God was telling me, and now I'm sharing with you is this.

25:49.405 --> 25:54.372
You don't have to do everything, but you can't do nothing.

25:57.616 --> 25:58.818
Friends, we can't do nothing.

26:02.002 --> 26:04.445
Nothing is not acceptable.

26:06.168 --> 26:08.050
And we are asked to do so much

26:08.322 --> 26:08.642
more.

26:09.764 --> 26:19.557
One of the things is I lead teams and teammates around here and kind of look at those systems is I have people say, well, you probably don't need help.

26:19.577 --> 26:20.258
We need help.

26:21.260 --> 26:21.981
Let me hear that.

26:22.081 --> 26:24.624
Let me let you hear that clear as day.

26:25.525 --> 26:27.588
But you want to know why people think we don't help?

26:28.089 --> 26:28.810
We don't need help?

26:29.571 --> 26:30.612
Because everything runs great.

26:31.694 --> 26:32.555
Everything looks good.

26:33.136 --> 26:33.496
Guess what?

26:33.556 --> 26:37.842
Your kids are taken care of because people serve their three and four times a month.

26:38.946 --> 26:39.206
Right?

26:39.266 --> 26:40.228
Your coffee's hot.

26:40.328 --> 26:40.688
Why?

26:40.768 --> 26:42.811
Because people come in at 730 to do it.

26:43.492 --> 26:54.486
What would it look like if God was calling you to do something in the here and the now that relieves some of that for other people in a sense of compassion?

26:55.567 --> 26:59.372
That you are moved to do something that you're like, it's not my time.

26:59.432 --> 27:00.393
It's not convenient.

27:00.693 --> 27:03.517
I don't want to, whatever it is, to say yes.

27:05.239 --> 27:07.442
That is what we're talking about today.

27:07.842 --> 27:12.288
Now hear me say that that doesn't, I'm not saying that because I want a bunch of people to join teams.

27:12.588 --> 27:13.429
I do want that.

27:13.890 --> 27:14.871
But you want to know why?

27:14.911 --> 27:18.596
Because I feel like that is a huge part of you being a part of this amazing body.

27:20.559 --> 27:23.904
And please hear me say that when you join one of our teams, you are not just a hand.

27:24.965 --> 27:31.494
You are a heart, you are a person, and you are needed to help us find and follow Jesus, which is our mission.

27:32.135 --> 27:34.738
Because we have to support each other in that.

27:34.946 --> 27:35.567
What do we know?

27:35.647 --> 27:36.327
What did we learn?

27:36.628 --> 27:38.009
We can't all do it by ourselves.

27:40.872 --> 27:44.135
Ezekiel and Moses both knew a king was coming.

27:44.876 --> 27:45.637
They were sure of it.

27:46.037 --> 27:46.778
They believed it.

27:47.699 --> 27:55.606
And they were waiting, and then in God's timing, Jesus fulfills the promises of Ezekiel and Moses, because he was the shepherd that they were waiting for.

27:56.647 --> 28:03.314
In John 10, 11, it says, I am the good shepherd, and the good shepherd lays down his life for the sheep.

28:06.050 --> 28:11.257
we sometimes have to lay down what is comfortable for our calling.

28:13.560 --> 28:23.294
If you would have said to me 10 years ago that this is where I would be standing, that was a full fledged timeout, no thank you, not my gift, all the things.

28:26.138 --> 28:29.062
What would I be missing if I wasn't living into my calling?

28:31.004 --> 28:35.090
A lot of speaking to four walls because I

28:36.258 --> 28:39.583
Impassionate about sharing the gospel in this way.

28:39.623 --> 28:41.867
And I'm, that's how God made me.

28:43.269 --> 28:48.396
So just like you can't do what you can't do, sometimes you have to do what you have to do.

28:51.361 --> 28:59.073
In T. Wright says, the cross is what happens when God's compassion meets human brokenness.

29:00.855 --> 29:02.057
Sit with that for a minute.

29:04.401 --> 29:05.202
The cross.

29:06.338 --> 29:24.741
The one that our Savior went to on our behalf is what happens because God loved us in all of His goodness and all of His compassion to send His one and only Son to meet our messy, to meet our brokenness.

29:25.742 --> 29:32.050
Do you know how He went to the cross willingly for us?

29:33.506 --> 29:38.492
Yet we can't seem to slow down to even notice someone needs us, let alone move towards it.

29:40.675 --> 29:44.339
See compassion didn't just move Jesus towards us.

29:46.122 --> 29:49.606
It held him there, all the way to the cross.

29:51.168 --> 29:53.030
You know whose sin held Jesus to the cross?

29:53.431 --> 29:53.671
Mine.

29:55.333 --> 29:59.879
Mine past, present, future sin held Jesus to the cross.

30:00.419 --> 30:01.581
Do you know who else is sin?

30:01.641 --> 30:02.482
Yours?

30:02.786 --> 30:04.508
everyone, the entire world.

30:05.288 --> 30:10.714
We serve the most gentle loving God because he did that for us.

30:11.554 --> 30:12.155
And you know what?

30:13.997 --> 30:19.142
I think he might say that he got to do it because he loves us so much.

30:19.422 --> 30:20.943
He knew that was the only way.

30:20.963 --> 30:28.711
He knew he was the bridge that would bridge that gap between us and sin.

30:28.771 --> 30:31.954
And he did it because he got to do it.

30:32.962 --> 30:38.168
And Romans says, while we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

30:39.149 --> 30:52.043
This is one of my all-time favorite verses that I remind myself over and over and over when I feel selfish, when I feel like I'm not enough, when I feel like what I'm doing doesn't matter.

30:52.083 --> 30:53.485
Like, wait, wait, wait.

30:54.806 --> 30:58.390
Well, I was still a sinner, which is still today.

30:58.471 --> 31:01.554
Christ died for me.

31:03.106 --> 31:11.254
He loves me that much, which means the compassion doesn't actually begin with us.

31:13.357 --> 31:14.558
It begins with God.

31:16.019 --> 31:30.194
And before Jesus even asked us to move towards anyone else, he's asking and calling us to move towards Him because He moves towards us.

31:31.906 --> 31:34.689
See, Jesus didn't wait for us to clean ourselves up.

31:37.251 --> 31:39.173
That's something else that we hear around here.

31:39.213 --> 31:48.282
Well, and then all these excuses of why I can't do the thing because I'm not old enough, I don't know enough, you don't know what I've done, blah, blah, blah.

31:48.322 --> 31:48.802
No, no, no, no.

31:49.803 --> 31:50.524
That is a lie.

31:51.345 --> 31:58.291
That is a lie of Satan that you do not deserve to serve anywhere in this kingdom because you do.

31:58.331 --> 32:01.234
That is a lie that you can't do something

32:01.794 --> 32:03.636
because you don't have it pulled together.

32:03.916 --> 32:04.857
Here's a noose flash.

32:05.177 --> 32:06.879
None of us have it pulled together.

32:06.899 --> 32:16.889
If I showed some hands, which don't raise them because I know they'd be out there, I'd be like, I barely held it together to get here this morning.

32:17.829 --> 32:19.311
Like you're lucky I'm even here at all.

32:19.691 --> 32:21.433
Yes, but guess what?

32:21.713 --> 32:22.454
You're here.

32:22.514 --> 32:25.297
And I am so glad that you're here.

32:26.738 --> 32:28.760
Jesus didn't wait for us to clean ourselves up.

32:29.060 --> 32:30.962
He stepped into us.

32:31.138 --> 32:32.440
at our worst.

32:33.562 --> 32:37.127
He steps toward us in our worst.

32:37.848 --> 32:38.930
And you know what that looks like?

32:39.711 --> 32:44.298
Sinful, harassed, helpless, wandering, cheap.

32:46.662 --> 32:51.950
Friends, that's who we are without a shepherd.

32:51.970 --> 32:52.931
But guess what we have?

32:54.033 --> 32:54.574
A shepherd.

32:55.575 --> 32:57.298
So we don't have to do that by ourselves.

32:58.114 --> 33:08.048
But also hear me say this morning that if you came in here this morning and you are tired, you are weary, you are tender, please know that we see you.

33:09.830 --> 33:11.212
We recognize that.

33:11.232 --> 33:16.960
If you feel harassed and helpless, we see you.

33:18.602 --> 33:22.588
We recognize that our hearts actually hurt for you.

33:25.792 --> 33:26.994
But also hear me say,

33:29.346 --> 33:45.182
that God also sees you, that God also hears you, that Jesus is the most kind, compassionate man you will ever meet, and he is moving towards you right now, and I do not want you to miss it.

33:47.744 --> 33:53.290
The cross is not just an example to follow, it's a gift to receive.

33:54.351 --> 33:55.111
Anybody else out there?

33:55.151 --> 33:57.714
Really terrible gift receivers?

33:58.274 --> 34:00.297
Some of us are, I'm actually, I feel like one of them.

34:00.778 --> 34:06.186
It's like that awkward open every time someone gives you a gift and don't know where to say thank you and then they're like, you're welcome and then it's like weird.

34:08.509 --> 34:13.617
What I'm saying is this is a gift that you don't have to say anything but yes.

34:16.922 --> 34:20.508
The story doesn't end at the cross.

34:21.489 --> 34:24.754
This is like my favorite part about who Jesus is.

34:25.890 --> 34:28.374
is that he didn't just go to the cross for us.

34:28.434 --> 34:29.897
That's not the end of the story.

34:30.297 --> 34:34.143
See, the resurrection means compassion didn't just forgive us.

34:34.524 --> 34:36.027
It transformed us.

34:36.547 --> 34:38.030
It made us different.

34:38.591 --> 34:47.986
And because of our relationship and who we are in Christ, we don't show compassion to earn God's love because we already have it.

34:48.930 --> 34:52.736
We show compassion because we've been overwhelmed by it.

34:53.176 --> 34:56.862
And it just comes so naturally that it pours out.

34:57.343 --> 35:01.950
And now that same compassion that saves us is what's sending us.

35:03.091 --> 35:05.876
It is sending us out into this city.

35:06.316 --> 35:15.410
Church, we cannot be a church of compassion and empathy and all the things that we've talked about and been for the mission if we don't,

35:15.490 --> 35:19.274
use compassion as just an armor that we wear.

35:19.935 --> 35:20.916
We can't do it.

35:21.417 --> 35:23.098
And we can't do it by ourselves.

35:25.221 --> 35:35.272
In Ephesians 2, 4, and 5, it says, but because of his great love for us, God, who is rich in mercy, made us alive with Christ.

35:35.612 --> 35:40.157
We are alive in Christ, and we are not alive in difference.

35:43.401 --> 35:44.402
So here's the ask.

35:45.890 --> 35:48.615
Here's the ask more than anything for me this morning.

35:48.735 --> 35:54.945
Do not leave here this morning thinking that I said you need to try harder.

35:56.768 --> 35:57.249
I didn't.

35:58.431 --> 35:59.833
And I don't want anybody to hear that.

36:00.695 --> 36:01.836
Because you know what the truth is?

36:01.877 --> 36:06.544
You can try all you want and without Jesus it doesn't matter.

36:06.564 --> 36:12.434
We need to decrease so he can increase.

36:13.282 --> 36:16.108
So it doesn't matter about how hard we try.

36:16.168 --> 36:33.522
So I don't want you to hear me say that, but the ask this morning is that we start to recognize the compassion that Jesus has for us, and we leave here changed today, right now, transformed by the compassion of Christ, and we take that

36:33.698 --> 36:47.311
to our families, and that to our schools, and that to our workplaces, and that to the hurt, and that to the oppressed, and that to the harassed, and that to the hopeless, because we shine the greatest light of Jesus that we possibly can.

36:47.411 --> 36:47.711
Why?

36:47.992 --> 36:49.273
Because he loved us first.

36:51.915 --> 37:02.506
So compassion begins when we stop seeing people's problems to solve, and simply start seeing them as sheep to love.

37:02.526 --> 37:03.026
That.

37:03.522 --> 37:10.089
is my ask of all of us this morning as we live into the mission and we do things with compassion.

37:10.710 --> 37:11.090
Let's pray.

37:13.633 --> 37:15.395
Lord, we are so grateful for who you are.

37:15.435 --> 37:18.679
We thank you for being our good shepherd.

37:19.800 --> 37:22.143
Lord, we know that we cannot do this life without you.

37:22.163 --> 37:27.048
And Lord, right now, we know that you are moving in this place.

37:27.088 --> 37:32.114
Holy Spirit, we know that you are moving

37:32.194 --> 37:42.109
and talking and nudging people's hearts in that guttural level of compassion, even maybe for ourselves.

37:43.070 --> 37:50.621
Lord, we can't love other people the way that you are asking us to love if we can't serve a gentle, compassionate Jesus.

37:52.103 --> 37:56.690
So this morning, Lord, as we sing this next song, I just pray that you

37:56.770 --> 38:07.186
will open hearts that you will break down walls and that you will have people encounter the beautiful, kind, compassionate Jesus that you are.

38:08.728 --> 38:10.170
Because Lord, we can't stay where we are.

38:11.412 --> 38:12.373
We can't do nothing.

38:13.475 --> 38:16.700
You are asking for movement and transformation.

38:16.740 --> 38:20.085
And Lord, we give that to you with open hands.

38:20.986 --> 38:26.194
Where we thank you for loving us and we thank you for the opportunity that we have just to come and worship you.

38:26.818 --> 38:29.316
We pray that all this in Jesus' name, amen.

38:29.820 --> 38:31.250
Would you guys stand so we can worship together?

